    • findClosestTextToken

      public WToken findClosestTextToken(WPoint p, boolean includeNonPrint)
      Return the closest text token to the point sx, sy (sign coordinates). If includeNonPrint is false, only printable text characters (including spaces and newlines) are included, otherwise all tokens that aren't text/color rectangles or graphics are included.

    • getLines

      public ArrayList<WTokenList> getLines()
      Return an ArrayList of WTokenLists containing the lines of the message in this list. Note that the [nl] tags ARE included at the end of each array.

    • getWords

      public ArrayList<WTokenList> getWords()
      Return an ArrayList of WTokenLists containing the words of the message in this list. Note that spaces are included at the end of each array. Non-text tags (including newlines) are also considered "words" by themselves.

    • findNextTextToken

      public WToken findNextTextToken(int si, boolean includeNewLine, boolean includeIrisTags)
      Return the next printable text token in the list after index si (inclusive - if the token at si is printable text, it is returned). If no tokens are found, null is returned. Includes newlines if includeNewLine is true, otherwise only WtTextChar tokens are included.

    • findFirstTextToken

      Find the first printable text token in the list.

    • findPrevTextToken

      public WToken findPrevTextToken(int si, boolean includeNewLine, boolean includeIrisTags)
      Return the previous printable text token in the list after index si (inclusive - if the token at si is printable text, it is returned). If no tokens are found, null is returned.
